 Drogba on Lyon radar
THE DAILY TELEGRAPHReigning French champions Lyon have become the first club to openly express an interest in Chelsea striker Didier Drogba. The departure of Jose Mourinho  to whom Drogba was especially close  has made him consider his own future at the club and the arrival of Dutch coach Henk ten Cate  to act as assistant to Mourinhos replacement Avram Grant  Drogba believes will change nothing. The breakdown of his relationship with the club, culminating in an interview with France Football in which he described Chelsea as broken and stated nothing can stop me from leaving now, has alerted Lyon to his potential availability. Lyon have tried to sign the player in the past with club president Jean-Michel Aulas saying to do so would be a dream. 
